---
description: Paperclip execution rules for Cursor coding lanes
alwaysApply: false
---

- Treat GitHub issues in `s6s8/provodnik.app-Tasks` as the scoped task contract for implementation.
- Work only inside the assigned worktree and issue branch.
- Follow `AGENTS.md`, `docs/process/orchestration-workflow.md`, and `docs/process/paperclip-agent-contract.md` before making planning assumptions.
- If the issue text is stale relative to `design/IMPLEMENTATION-GUIDE.md` or `design/STAKEHOLDER-FEEDBACK.md`, stop and push that mismatch back to the tracker or CTO instead of freelancing a plan.
- Keep changes confined to the expected paths for the assigned area.
- Return:
  - changed files
  - checks run
  - blockers
  - remaining risk
- Do not update Slack directly from Cursor lanes.
- Do not close GitHub issues from Cursor lanes.
